channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Fox News projects Democrat Tammy Baldwin survives tight race to hold Wisconsin Senate seat
item.description: The Fox News Decision Desk projects that Tammy Baldwin fended off a competitive challenge for her Senate seat from businessman Eric Hovde.

item.title: Awkward: Canadian PM Justin Trudeau congratulates Trump on victory
item.description: Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau is congratulating President-elect Donald Trump on his victory, a nod to their countries' close relationship despite their personal animus over the years.

item.title: Let Trump’s Resounding Victory Be the End of Lawfare
item.description: Biden should pardon Trump, as he (inevitably) pardons his son.

item.title: The Media Concede Kamala’s Defeat. Now They Need To Fully Surrender If They Want To Be Spared
item.description: There won't be an apology and even as they concede Kamala's defeat, they won't do what's needed — a full and unconditional surrender.

item.title: GOP challenger unseats Rep. Susan Wild in Pennsylvania
item.description: Pennsylvania Democratic Rep. Susan Wild faced Republican challenger Ryan Mackenzie for the 7th Congressional District seat in the Keystone State.

item.title: Americans search for options to flee U.S. after Trump win
item.description: Presumptive President-elect Donald Trump's historic election night has sparked a new interest in immigration -- but this time it's Americans looking to get out.

item.title: What to Pay Attention to in the Election Results
item.description: History will conclude that the two people who could not beat Donald Trump in 2024 were the two the Democrats tried to run.

item.title: It’s Unacceptable That Kamala Harris Hasn’t Yet Publicly Accepted The Results Of The 2024 Election
item.description: The Democrats’ replacement candidate has been missing in action since her Election Day loss to Donald Trump.

item.title: Pennsylvania Democrat Rep. Matt Cartwright concedes race to GOP challenger
item.description: Democrat Pennsylvania Rep. Matt Cartwright faced Republican challenger, local businessman, Rob Bresnahan in the race for the state's 8th Congressional District seat.

item.title: Liz Cheney accepts election results, urges media, judges to become 'guardrails of democracy'
item.description: Former Rep. Liz Cheney, the onetime GOP leader who bolted to become one of Democrats' biggest cheerleaders this year, said Wednesday she accepts the results of the election -- but urged ongoing resistance "over these coming four years."

item.title: Can Democrats Break Out of Their Echo Chamber?
item.description: Kamala Harris and her party have no one to blame but themselves for their misfortune.

item.title: Veteran Tim Sheehy Ousts Three-Term Democrat Sen. Jon Tester In Montana
item.description: Veteran Tim Sheehy, endorsed by former President Donald Trump, defeated Montana's long-time Democrat Sen. Jon Tester.

item.title: California DA Pamela Price recalled over 'progressive leftist' crime policies
item.description: Alameda County residents voted to oust District Attorney Pamela Price on Wednesday. Oakland Mayor Sheng Thao was also ousted from office.

item.title: Democrats hold onto House seat in Michigan with Kristen McDonald Rivet
item.description: In the neighboring Michigan's 8th District, perennial Republican candidate Paul Junge lost his third straight House race early Wednesday.

item.title: European Economic Sclerosis Is Here to Stay
item.description: It would seem to be only a matter of time before the euro zone experiences another round of the sovereign-debt crisis — this time centered on France and Italy.

item.title: Voters Across The Country Take A Sledgehammer To Ranked-Choice Voting Initiatives
item.description: Voters overwhelmingly defeated ballot initiatives seeking to implement ranked-choice voting in numerous states across the country.

item.title: 'Got our a--es kicked': Dems privately fret about losing House after GOP victory in White House, Senate
item.description: Democrats are growing increasingly concerned that their path to flipping the House of Representatives is narrowing.

item.title: Muslim coalition celebrates Kamala Harris' loss, says she chose 'blood over humanity'
item.description: A coalition of Muslim and Arab-American leaders who worked to defeat Vice President Kamala Harris crowed Wednesday morning over her loss.

item.title: Julia Roberts, Home-Wrecker, Nation-Destroyer
item.description: ‘Your Turn, Honey’ promotes a movie star’s anti-American revolt.

item.title: Midwest Voters Side With Unborn Babies On State Ballot Measures
item.description: Voters in two Midwest states, Nebraska and South Dakota, defeated measures to expand abortion.
